## Edge cases

- **Agent has access to a mutating tool** (writes a file, sends an email,
  charges a card): every mutation tool requires `--dry-run` mode AND a
  human-in-the-loop confirmation step in the state machine, unless the agent
  is explicitly declared autonomous in the task spec.
- **Browser-driving agent** (cross-references `/agent-browser`,
  `/open-gstack-browser`): tool list includes the full browse command
  surface; precondition is "browser session active"; cost model includes
  network latency.
- **Agent that spawns sub-agents** (Anthropic pattern): set a max-depth cap
  (3 is sane); each child has its own state machine instance; results are
  summarized through a structured-output schema.
- **Reflexion memory leak:** failure traces are summarized after each
  attempt, never raw-concatenated. Token budget per memory: 1000 tokens max.
- **Long-running agent** (> 5 min): persist state to disk every transition
  so crash-recovery is possible. Use a typed durable-execution lib if you
  have one (Temporal, Inngest); otherwise a versioned JSON file.

